WalkQuest — Feature-wise TODOs (iOS)
App Foundation [complete]

 [x] Project setup: Swift 5.9+, SwiftUI, Combine, iOS 17 min target, modular structure.

 [x] Networking: typed API client (async/await), request/response models, retries + exponential backoff.

 [x] Secure storage: Keychain for tokens, on-device cache for quests (SQLite/GRDB).

 [x] Feature flags: remote toggles for verification vendors & experiments.

 [x] Crash/metrics: Crashlytics/Sentry + custom events.

Onboarding & Auth [complete]

 [x] Sign-in: Apple Sign In + optional email OTP.

 [x] Permissions flows: Location (When In Use + Precise), Camera, Motion. Pre-permission education screens.

 [x] Profile bootstrap: username, avatar (auto-generate if skipped).

Home / “Today’s Quest”

 Quest feed: pull daily quests; show distance, difficulty, reward.

 Location picker: MapKit view with user dot, quest pins, distance indicators, “Navigate” deep link to Apple Maps.

 Eligibility rules: lock “Go!” until user within quest radius; show live distance.

 Caching: offline list + stale-while-revalidate refresh.

Capture & Proof Submission

 In-app camera: AVFoundation capture, gridlines, exposure lock, no gallery import.

 Auto-attach sensors: last 3s GPS samples, heading, pitch/roll (CoreMotion), EXIF.

 Upload pipeline: multipart to /proofs, progressive UI states (Uploading → Verifying → Result).

 UI nudge: show “face the landmark / include sign” hints per quest.

 Failure UX: clear reason + one-tap retry.

Server Verification (cloud, no local CV)

 GPS sanity: speed/jumps, inside geofence, timestamp drift check.

 VPS pose: integrate vendor (e.g., Google Geospatial / Lightship) where coverage exists; store pose quality + heading diff.

 Vision layer:

Landmarks → Cloud Vision Landmark API.

Generic quests → multimodal LLM (Gemini or GPT-4o) with quest text + map tile + photo.

 Decision engine: weighted pass with thresholds; return reason codes.

 Rate limiting & abuse: per-user and per-device caps.

Scoring, Streaks, Badges

 Points calc: base points + distance/difficulty multipliers.

 Streak logic: soft grace window (e.g., 36h) to reduce churn.

 Badges: unlocks for first week, 10 quests, new area, rain day, etc.

Leaderboard

 Views: global, city, friends. Time windows: daily/weekly/all-time.

 Pagination: server-side rank window around user.

 Privacy: display name controls; opt-out toggle.

Notifications

 Push setup: APNs tokens, topic per city.

 Nudges: “quest nearby,” “streak expiring,” “friend overtook you.”

 Quiet hours: user setting + city-aware scheduling.

Settings & Profile

 Edit profile: name, avatar, bio.

 Privacy toggles: face-blur on server, photo retention window, leaderboard visibility.

 Data export/delete: request account data, delete account flow.

 About: version, licenses, support.

Anti-Cheat & Integrity

 In-app capture enforcement: block Photos access; verify EXIF vs server time.

 Device attestation: App Attest / DeviceCheck; flag jailbroken signals.

 Screen-photo detection: LLM check for bezels/UI moiré; raise suspicion score.

 Path check: minimal breadcrumb to ensure arrival via plausible movement.

 High-value challenges: randomized pose request (“include gate on left”).

Content & Quest Ops

 CMS: create/curate quests with radius, hint text, reward, vendor coverage flag.

 Geo health: coverage heatmap (VPS areas), fallback to generic “ambient quests” where coverage is weak.

 A/B experiments: hint text variants, radius sizes, reward curves.

Analytics & Experimentation

 Event schema: view_quest, attempt_capture, verify_pass/fail (reason), points_awarded, streak_change.

 Funnels: Home → Go! → Capture → Upload → Pass.

 Cohort dashboards: D1/D7 retention, average quests/user/week, fail reasons heatmap by district.

Offline & Resilience

 Graceful degrade: queue proofs when offline, retry with jitter.

 Timeout UX: verification SLA, user feedback, fallback retry.

 Idempotency: client nonce to avoid double scoring.

Moderation & Safety

 Photo moderation: auto-blur faces; disallow explicit/offensive content (vendor moderation).

 Location safety: avoid quests near tracks/highways/private property; time-of-day rules.

 Report flow: report quest/photo/user; admin triage.

Legal & Privacy

 Transparent policy: what we collect (GPS, photo, sensors), why, retention defaults.

 Consent: first-run consent with per-permission toggles.

 Data retention: default 24–72h for raw photos unless user opts to save to profile.

Payments (optional, later)

 IAP: cosmetic badges/themes; no pay-to-win scores.

 Promos: brand quests with disclosures; separate leaderboard.

DevEx, QA, Release

 API contracts: OpenAPI spec; mock server for UI dev.

 Unit/UI tests: camera controller, permission flows, leaderboard windowing.

 CI/CD: fastlane, TestFlight lanes, symbol upload, feature-flagged builds.

 Load test: verify endpoints under burst (evening peaks).
